CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 15, 1954, pg. 17 reads: "Teen-age Disc Jockey - Charles Alexander, 2100 Federal Street, North Side, appeared as a teen-aged disc jockey on radio Station WJAS last week as the result of being elected to serve on the "Dial for Style" program by the votes of youngsters. He was the guest of Hillary Bogdan, shown with him at the turntable. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Hillary Bogdan, standing next to Charles Alexander, elected to serve on the "Dial for Style" program, seated at turntables in WJAS
